<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="55">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="55">vagina</emphasis>
(Latin) = sheath. Possibly referring to the conspicuous leaf-sheaths, a feature that is common to most of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
